name: Xonox Double Ender: Artillery Duel/Chuck Norris Superkicks
overview: Artillery Duel is a two player game of skill and strategy as you try to knock out your enemy's gun emplacement. New random terrains in each battle! Chuck Norris Superkicks is a 1983 video game produced by Xonox where the player takes control of Chuck Norris. It was later sold as Kung Fu Superkicks when the license for the use of the name Chuck Norris expired. The game was produced for the Commodore 64, Commodore VIC-20, Atari 2600, and Colecovision as part of Xonox's double-ender cartridge line (cartridges with two games and two connectors that were flipped over depending on which one the user wanted to play).
